{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a premium mobile-first educational statistics section for Ariya Supplements’ sleep product, Calm Nights.The design should feel similar to premium DTC wellness brands like Ritual, Eight Sleep, AG1, and Momentous.The section should be extremely easy to scan in under 5 seconds on mobile.Use lots of white space, clean typography, rounded corners, subtle shadows, and a luxury wellness aesthetic.DO NOT use bright colors, clutter, decorative graphics, or complex illustrations.SECTION HEADLINEYour Brain Wasn’t Designed For Modern Life.Color: BlackLarge bold headline.This should be the first thing visitors notice.SUPPORTING TEXTLate-night scrolling. Constant notifications. Endless stimulation.Color: Dark gray.Centered beneath the headline.STATISTICS SECTIONCreate three statistic cards displayed side-by-side on desktop and stacked vertically on mobile.Use white cards with subtle shadows and rounded corners.The large statistic numbers should be Ariya purple and serve as the visual focus.The supporting text should be dark gray or black.STATISTIC CARD 1Icon:Simple outline brain icon.Only a brain.No light bulbs.
    No faces.
    No emojis.
    No decorative graphics.Statistic:48%Supporting Text:of U.S. adults report lying awake at night due to stress.STATISTIC CARD 2Icon:Three people with one person highlighted.The icon should clearly communicate “1 in 3.”Do not use abstract shapes.Statistic:1 in 3Supporting Text:adults don’t get enough sleep on a regular basis.STATISTIC CARD 3Icon:Simple crescent moon icon.Only a crescent moon.No stars.
    No dots.
    No decorative elements.Statistic:50–70 MillionSupporting Text:Americans struggle with chronic sleep issues.TRANSITION TEXTModern life makes it harder than ever to slow down and relax before bed.Centered beneath the statistics cards.Color: dark gray.CTA SECTIONCreate a separate section beneath the statistics.Use a very light purple background.Headline:That’s Why We Created Calm Nights.Body Text:Melatonin-free sleep support designed to help quiet a racing mind, promote relaxation, and help you wake up refreshed.Button:Shop Calm NightsButton Color:Ariya PurpleButton should be the strongest visual element in the CTA section.BENEFITS ROWUnder the button create four simple benefit icons with short labels.Use matching outline icons.Benefit 1:
    Leaf icon
    Melatonin-FreeBenefit 2:
    Lotus or calming icon
    Promotes RelaxationBenefit 3:
    Brain icon
    Supports a Calm MindBenefit 4:
    Sunrise icon
    Wake Up RefreshedIMPORTANT DESIGN RULES80% neutral colors.
    20% Ariya purple.Keep the headline black.Keep supporting text dark gray.Keep the statistics purple.Keep the icons simple and minimal.Do not use:Light bulbsFacesAbstract symbolsDecorative illustrationsComplex graphicsUse only:
     Brain
     Three people with one highlighted
     Crescent moonThe visual story should be:Stress → People affected → Sleep problems → Calm Nights solution., the symbol for 1 in 3, change that to an outline of a human as the symbol, where it says melatonin free the symbol right now is a plus sign with a circle around it, can you change that to a leaf symbol abov the melatonin free, can you align this section with the other ones it is shifted to the left too much and be sure to keep it mobile friendly and fix the shift for the desktop, Center the entire “Your Brain Wasn’t Designed For Modern Life” section.
    The statistics cards are currently shifted slightly to the left and do not align with the rest of the page.
    Ensure the headline, subheadline, statistic cards, transition text, and CTA are all contained within the same centered container.
    Use equal left and right spacing.
    The three statistic cards should be perfectly balanced across the page.
    The center card should sit directly under the center of the headline.
    The left and right cards should have equal spacing from the edges of the section.
    Keep the current card sizes and styling, but fix the alignment so the entire section feels centered and symmetrical on desktop and mobile.
    Match the horizontal alignment used in the Benefits section and Comparison section.
    One more thing:
    Looking at the screenshot, I’d also have it:
    Increase the max width of the statistics section by approximately 10–15%.
    Right now there’s a lot of empty white space on both sides of the cards. Widening the section slightly will make it feel more intentional and premium on desktop., change the button that says shop calm nights to when you press it it take you up to the top and doesnt load a new page, for melatonin free at the bottom change the symbol to a leaf and for promotes relaxation change the symbol to a smiley face and align them in a row of two next to each other
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  .ai-stats-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    padding: {{ block.settings.section_padding_mobile }}px 20px;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
  }

  .ai-stats-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    max-width: {{ block.settings.max_width }}px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ai-stats-headline-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.headline_size_mobile }}px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: {{ block.settings.headline_color }};
    margin: 0 0 {{ block.settings.headline_spacing }}px 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .ai-stats-subtext-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.subtext_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.subtext_color }};
    margin: 0 0 {{ block.settings.subtext_spacing }}px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .ai-stats-cards-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: {{ block.settings.card_gap_mobile }}px;
    margin-bottom: {{ block.settings.cards_spacing }}px;
  }

  .ai-stats-card-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.card_background }};
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.card_border_radius }}px;
    padding: {{ block.settings.card_padding_mobile }}px;
    box-shadow: {{ block.settings.card_shadow }};
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: {{ block.settings.card_content_gap }}px;
  }

  .ai-stats-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    width: {{ block.settings.icon_size_mobile }}px;
    height: {{ block.settings.icon_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.icon_color }};
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ai-stats-number-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.stat_size_mobile }}px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: {{ block.settings.stat_color }};
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .ai-stats-description-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.description_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.description_color }};
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .ai-stats-transition-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.transition_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.transition_color }};
    margin: 0 0 {{ block.settings.transition_spacing }}px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .ai-stats-cta-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.cta_background }};
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.cta_border_radius }}px;
    padding: {{ block.settings.cta_padding_mobile }}px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: {{ block.settings.cta_content_gap }}px;
  }

  .ai-stats-cta-headline-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.cta_headline_size_mobile }}px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: {{ block.settings.cta_headline_color }};
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .ai-stats-cta-body-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.cta_body_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.cta_body_color }};
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .ai-stats-cta-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.button_color }};
    color: {{ block.settings.button_text_color }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.button_size_mobile }}px;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: {{ block.settings.button_padding_mobile }}px {{ block.settings.button_padding_mobile | times: 1.5 }}px;
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.button_border_radius }}px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .ai-stats-cta-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.button_hover_color }};
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(60, 14, 102, 0.2);
  }

  .ai-stats-benefits-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: {{ block.settings.benefits_gap_mobile }}px;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .ai-stats-benefit-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: {{ block.settings.benefit_content_gap }}px;
  }

  .ai-stats-benefit-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    width: {{ block.settings.benefit_icon_size_mobile }}px;
    height: {{ block.settings.benefit_icon_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.benefit_icon_color }};
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ai-stats-benefit-label-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.benefit_label_size_mobile }}px;
    color: {{ block.settings.benefit_label_color }};
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.4;
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .ai-stats-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: {{ block.settings.section_padding_desktop }}px 40px;
    }

    .ai-stats-headline-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.headline_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-subtext-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.subtext_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-cards-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: {{ block.settings.card_gap_desktop }}px;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .ai-stats-card-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      flex: 1;
      max-width: 320px;
      padding: {{ block.settings.card_padding_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      width: {{ block.settings.icon_size_desktop }}px;
      height: {{ block.settings.icon_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-number-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.stat_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-description-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.description_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-transition-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.transition_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-cta-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: {{ block.settings.cta_padding_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-cta-headline-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.cta_headline_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-cta-body-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.cta_body_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-cta-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.button_size_desktop }}px;
      padding: {{ block.settings.button_padding_desktop }}px {{ block.settings.button_padding_desktop | times: 2 }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-benefits-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: {{ block.settings.benefits_gap_desktop }}px;
      max-width: 800px;
    }

    .ai-stats-benefit-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      width: {{ block.settings.benefit_icon_size_desktop }}px;
      height: {{ block.settings.benefit_icon_size_desktop }}px;
    }

    .ai-stats-benefit-label-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.benefit_label_size_desktop }}px;
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

